Class.name: Custom.SWARH.HIPS.ws.v1.q60.PatientParticipationResponse
Class.Description: <summary> This class is the response from HIPS for a request to get the PCEHR participation status, either for a single patient or for all patients with recent changes to their records. </summary> Created from: http://sahipsh00.swarh.net:50500/HIPSServer_TEST/HIPS.Service.PCEHRService.svc?xsd=xsd10

Property.name: PatientParticipationList
Property.Description: <summary> The information required for the calling system to identify one or more patient records and their current PCEHR participation status. </summary>

Property.name: Response
Property.Description: <summary> Gets or sets an indicator of success or failure and in case of failure, the reason for the failure. </summary>
